<TITLE> Usha take solo lead in Premier Hockey </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 18 (bdnews24.com)  Usha Krira Chakra took solo lead in the Premier Division Hockey League when they handed a 2-0 defeat to Dhaka Mariner Youngs at Moulana Bhasani National Stadium Sunday. With the seventh straight win, Usha increased their lead to 21 points, two points in advance of Abahani Limited and three points ahead of third-paced Mohammedan. Jahidul Islam Rajon converted a penalty corner in the 14th minute to give Usha a lead before Pakistani Tariq Aziz made it 2-0 to seal the match. In the other match of the day, Ajax SC tasted first triumph with an emphatic 4-1 win over Azad SC, who went two goals down in the first half. Rahat Sarwar struck two goals while Imtiaz Ahmed Rubel and Mahbubul Alam Robin netted one goal each for Ajax. Hasan Jubair scored the lone goal for Azad SC. 
